# Slab docs addendum

## Source of truth

- Always verify documentation against theme source code before writing.
- Use `.liquid` files, `{% schema %}` settings, and locale keys as canonical references.
- If required source files are not accessible, ask for those exact paths before drafting content.
- Do not guess block behavior, defaults, compatibility, or setting labels.

## Slab-specific checks

- Resolve translated labels (`t:` keys) using Slab locale files before writing setting names.
- Confirm compatibility claims (nesting, supported block types, app-block support) from schema and Liquid usage.
- Verify defaults, ranges, and option values from `{% schema %}` before documenting.
- If behavior differs by template/context, state that condition explicitly in the docs.

## Scope

- This file only adds Slab-specific verification guidance.
- Use global docs rules for structure, formatting, and writing style.
